%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimmediately%20after%20election%20day%3C%2Fa%3E.%20An%20astounding%20%2422.3%20billion%20went%20into%20US%20ETFs%20last%20Wednesday%2C%20and%20BlackRock's%20uber-popular%20iShares%20Russell%202000%20ETF%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fetfs%2Fishares-russell-2000-etf-us4642876555%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIWM%3C%2Fa%3E)%20had%20its%20most%20active%20day%20of%20trading%20and%20inflows%20since%202007%20as%20small%20caps%20soared%20by%205.8%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20BlackRock's%20Gargi%20Chaudhuri%20doesn't%20think%20President-elect%20Trump%20deserves%20all%20the%20credit%20for%20this%20astounding%20market%20rally.%20The%20chief%20investment%20and%20portfolio%20strategist%2C%20Americas%20noted%20in%20a%20recent%20interview%20that%20US%20stocks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-rally-outlook-trump-win-investing-strategy-2025-page-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehad%20several%20strong%20catalysts%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20Trump's%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20there%20have%20been%20some%20pretty%20sharp%20movements%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20last%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20Chaudhuri%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BBut%20even%20as%20we%20look%20back%20to%20the%20quarter%20before%20that%20or%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20this%20year%2C%20I%20think%20there%20have%20been%20some%20very%20solid%20fundamentals%20that%20have%20underpinned%20this%20movement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobust%20growth%20for%20the%20economy%20and%20corporate%20earnings%20are%20some%20of%20the%20most%20salient%20market%20drivers%2C%20as%20are%20lower%20interest%20rates%20and%20receding%20inflation%2C%20Chaudhuri%20said.%20End-of-year%20rallies%20are%20also%20very%20common%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-outlook-history-yearend-rally-election-trump-harris-truist-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eespecially%20in%20strong%20years%20for%20the%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20Truist%20recently%20remarked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20convincing%20explanation%20for%20this%20recent%20market%20momentum%20is%20that%20investors%20had%20reduced%20risk%20as%20uncertainty%20mounted%20ahead%20of%20the%20election%20before%20quickly%20changing%20course%20when%20they%20got%20clarity%20on%20the%20path%20forward%20sooner%20and%20more%20decisively%20than%20anticipated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInvestors%20bringing%20down%20their%20portfolio%20risk%20going%20into%20elections%20was%20perhaps%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20that%20we%20have%20seen%20this%20pretty%20strong%20re-risking%20in%20markets%2C%20especially%20after%20we%20got%20the%20election%20results%2C%26quot%3B%20Chaudhuri%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e1cf1135-8543-44c9-9cf9-a679564fb91f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20softer%20economic%20readings%20are%20a%20red%20herring%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20new%20year%20approaches%2C%20Chaudhuri%20is%20rather%20confident%20about%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20even%20though%20a%20few%20recent%20developments%20seem%20to%20have%20given%20the%20glass-half-empty%20camp%20some%20ammunition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGDP%20growth%20and%20job%20additions%20have%20slipped%20lately%2C%20though%20neither%20is%20a%20major%20cause%20for%20concern%20for%20Chaudhuri.%20The%20economy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgdp-gross-domestic-product-third-quarter-economy-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edidn't%20expand%20as%20much%20as%20expected%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20GDP%20still%20rose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftradingeconomics.com%2Funited-states%2Fgdp-growth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eat%20a%20healthy%20clip%20of%202.8%25%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foctober-jobs-report-unemployment-rate-nonfarm-payroll-growth-federal-reserve-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweak%20October%20jobs%20figure%3C%2Fa%3E%20appears%20to%20be%20largely%20due%20to%20the%20severe%20weather%20events%20that%20disrupted%20thousands%20of%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20more%20modest%20growth%20is%20a%20sign%20that%20the%20economy%20isn't%20overheating%2C%20which%20is%20welcome%20news%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20in%20its%20quest%20to%20ease%20financial%20conditions%20without%20reviving%20inflation.%20Such%20moderations%20aren't%20giving%20Chaudhuri%20pause%20about%20the%20trajectory%20of%20the%20US%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20very%20normal%20for%20us%20to%20continue%20to%20see%20a%20further%20normalization%20in%20the%20labor%20market%2C%20given%20how%20strong%20the%20economy%20has%20already%20been%2C%20how%20high%20rates%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Chaudhuri%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20investment%20chief%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20haven't%20really%20seen%20that%20job%20destruction%20taking%20place%20quite%20yet.%20You're%20still%20seeing%20wages%20rising%3B%20you're%20not%20seeing%20layoffs%20pick%20up%20in%20a%20meaningful%20manner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorporate%20earnings%20growth%20is%20arguably%20the%20most%20compelling%20reason%20to%20stick%20with%20US%20stocks%20following%20what's%20been%20another%20outstanding%20performance%20this%20year.%20Profits%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-rally-outlook-trump-win-investing-strategy-2025-page-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejumped%20about%207%25%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20well%20above%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-invest-q3-earnings-season-recession-risk-investing-strategy-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emid-single-digit%20figure%20that%20analysts%20were%20banking%20on%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20things%20that%20the%20equity%20market%20has%20done%20over%20and%20over%20again%20is%20continue%20to%20surprise%20us%20in%20terms%20of%20earnings%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Chaudhuri%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20companies%20have%20continued%20to%20find%20very%20innovative%20ways%20to%20manage%20their%20expenses.%20They've%20found%20a%20way%2C%20especially%20given%20the%20spend%20on%20AI%2C%20the%20type%20of%20CapEx%20that's%20going%20into%20finding%20ways%20to%20make%20companies%20have%20more%20productivity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221bb5d4ad-c973-49dc-9ddc-4fb0e9f732a3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20to%20invest%20in%20a%20rosy%202025%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20sectors%20with%20abnormally%20strong%20earnings%20prospects%20are%20%3Cstrong%3Efinancials%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20and%20%3Cstrong%3Eindustrials%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20Chaudhuri%20said.%20These%20economically%20sensitive%20groups%20enjoyed%20some%20of%20the%20larger%20post-election%20pops%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-invest-trump-win-election-stock-market-outlook-strategy-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20puts%20its%20chips%20on%20sectors%20that%20should%20benefit%20from%20a%20hot%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20although%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcheap-stocks-to-buy-strong-growth-market-outlook-garp-bmo-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmaller%20stocks%20have%20been%20on%20a%20heater%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Chaudhuri%20believes%20that%20%3Cstrong%3Elarge%2C%20undervalued%20companies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20are%20the%20better%20place%20to%20be%2C%20given%20their%20superior%20earnings%20setup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20a%20longer%20period%20of%20time%2C%20large%20cap%20is%20where%20we%20think%20the%20earnings%20growth%20is%20going%20to%20continue%20to%20be%20higher%20and%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Chaudhuri%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20earnings%20may%20not%20be%20under%20the%20microscope%20like%20they%20were%20when%20interest%20rates%20were%20at%20their%20peak%2C%20they're%20still%20top%20of%20mind%20for%20Chaudhuri.%20Larger%20stocks%20often%20have%20better%20earnings%20than%20their%20smaller%20peers%2C%20and%20the%20investment%20chief%20thinks%20that%20the%20cream%20will%20eventually%20rise%20to%20the%20top.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20catch-up%20trade%20that's%20happening%20in%20small%20caps%20right%20now%20has%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20legs%2C%26quot%3B%20Chaudhuri%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20can%20continue%2C%20maybe%20'til%20the%20end%20of%20this%20month%20or%20even%20the%20end%20of%20next%20month.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChaudhuri%20continued%3A%20%26quot%3BBut%20for%20us%20to%20believe%20in%20sustained%20rallies%20in%20small%20caps%2C%20we%20would%20need%20to%20see%20earnings%20growth%2C%20and%20over%2050%25%20of%20the%20small-cap%20index%20still%20is%20not%20very%20profitable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-invest-2025-stock-market-outlook-strategy-blackrock-chaudhuri-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731663002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67365ecffa0140cdd56390c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-invest-2025-stock-market-outlook-strategy-blackrock-chaudhuri-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22BlackRock's%20Gargi%20Chaudhuri%20is%20optimistic%20about%20economic%20growth%20ahead%20of%202025.%20Here's%20where%20investors%20should%20put%20their%20money%20during%20a%20major%20rally.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jfaris%40businessinsider.com%20(James%20Faris)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-invest-2025-stock-market-outlook-strategy-blackrock-chaudhuri-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22McDonald's%20wants%20to%20make%20flatulent%20cows%20less%20of%20a%20problem%20for%20the%20environment%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22McDonald's%20Big%20Mac%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e2a0ecfe0e1441aaa112de3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMcDonald's%20is%20working%20with%20Syngenta%20to%20reduce%20gas%20emissions%20from%20the%20cattle%20that%20produce%20its%20burger%20meat.%3Cp%3EIrene%20Jiang%20%2F%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freview-signature-burgers-mcdonalds-burger-king-wendys-2023-4%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBurgers%20at%20McDonald's%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20soon%20involve%20fewer%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20thanks%20to%20a%20new%20cattle%20feed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20of%20the%20restaurant's%20meat%20suppliers%20will%20use%20a%20new%20type%20of%20corn%20from%20seed%20company%20Syngenta.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20feed%20could%20reduce%20carbon%20dioxide%20emissions%20and%20water%20consumed%20while%20raising%20the%20cattle.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20McDonald's%20customer%20hopefully%20isn't%20thinking%20about%20the%20impact%20that%20cattle%20burps%20%E2%80%94%20or%20worse%20%E2%80%94%20can%20have%20on%20the%20environment%20as%20they%20chow%20down%20on%20a%20Big%20Mac.%20The%20company%2C%20however%2C%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freview-mcdonalds-spicy-chicken-nuggets-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20working%20with%20seed%20company%20Syngenta%20and%20Lopez%20Foods%2C%20one%20of%20McDonald's%20meat%20suppliers%2C%20to%20feed%20cattle%20Syngenta's%20Enogen%20corn%2C%20the%20companies%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesswire.com%2Fnews%2Fhome%2F20241114754025%2Fen%2FMcDonald%25E2%2580%2599s-USA-Syngenta-and-Lopez-Foods-Collaborate-to-Help-Produce-Beef-More-Sustainably-in-the-US%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnogen%20is%20a%20feed%20that%20has%20been%20genetically%20modified%20with%20an%20enzyme%20%26quot%3Bthat%20quickly%20converts%20starch%20to%20usable%20sugars%2C%20delivering%20more%20available%20energy%20to%20cattle%20while%20being%20easily%20digestible%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20easy%20digestibility%20could%20mean%20fewer%20greenhouse%20gases%2C%20which%20contribute%20to%20global%20warming.%20As%20cattle%20and%20other%20livestock%20digest%20food%2C%20they%20produce%20methane%2C%20usually%20through%20belching%20or%20flatulence%2C%20which%20represents%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20all%20the%20agriculture%20industry's%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fghgemissions%2Fsources-greenhouse-gas-emissions%23agriculture%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEnvironmental%20Protection%20Agency.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20well%20as%20potentially%20fewer%20bovine%20burps%2C%20cattle%20that%20eat%20Enogen%20corn%20can%20also%20reach%20slaughtering%20weight%20faster%20and%20with%20a%20smaller%20environmental%20footprint%2C%20according%20to%20the%20companies.%20Syngenta%20said%20that%20a%20herd%20of%201%2C000%20cattle%20fed%20using%20Enogen%20could%20result%20in%20196%20fewer%20tons%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20emitted%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20and%206%20million%20fewer%20gallons%20of%20water%20consumed%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcDonald's%20said%20the%20feed%20could%20help%20it%20meet%20its%20climate%20goals.%20The%20fast-food%20chain%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporate.mcdonalds.com%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Fsites%2Fcorp%2Fnfl%2Fpdf%2FMcDonalds-2023-Climate-Resiliency-Summary.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etargeting%20net-zero%20emissions%20by%202050%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20has%20said%20it%20will%20cut%20emissions%20from%20its%20company-owned%20restaurants%20and%20offices%20by%20about%2050%25%20by%202030%2C%20among%20other%20goals.%20It's%20a%20top%20buyer%20of%20beef%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20the%20innovative%20collaboration%20with%20Syngenta%20is%20an%20opportunity%20to%20help%20us%20make%20progress%20toward%20our%20science-based%20climate%20targets%2C%26quot%3B%20Director%20of%20US%20Sustainability%20for%20McDonald's%20Kendra%20Levine%20said%20in%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-sales-dropped-second-quarter-in-a-row-sharees-down-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%20global%20sales%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20down%20during%20the%20company's%20third%20quarter%20as%20many%20consumers%20saved%20money%20by%20eating%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20burger%20chain%20won%20back%20some%20customers%20with%20its%20temporary%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-promises-more-value-menu-deals-to-win-back-customers-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%245%20meal%20deal%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20which%20excluded%20the%20two-beef-patty%20McDouble%20burger.%20Executives%20have%20said%20they're%20planning%20permanent%20changes%20to%20McDonald's%20menu%20to%20offer%20more%20affordable%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-beef-supplier-to-use-gm-corn-lower-cattle-emissions-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731662702000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673662bfede4eeae3927ac2f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-beef-supplier-to-use-gm-corn-lower-cattle-emissions-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20McDonald's%20meat%20supplier%20will%20use%20a%20new%20corn%20feed%20that%20could%20reduce%20the%20environmental%20impact%20of%20raising%20beef%20cattle.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abitter%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Bitter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-beef-supplier-to-use-gm-corn-lower-cattle-emissions-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Get%20to%20the%20office%20if%20you%20want%20a%20promotion%2C%20ex-Google%20CEO%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223300%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Former%20chairman%20and%20CEO%20of%20Google%2C%20Eric%20Schmidt.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664edbad20abc1efe8fcc396%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222198%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEric%20Schmidt%2C%20Google's%20former%20CEO%2C%20explained%20why%20he%20was%20a%20vocal%20proponent%20of%20in-office%20work.%3Cp%3EShahar%20Azran%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EEric%20Schmidt%20partly%20credits%20his%20time%20in%20the%20office%20for%20his%20promotions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESchmidt%20said%20in-person%20work%20offers%20experiences%20crucial%20for%20career%20advancement.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMajor%20tech%20companies%20have%20cracked%20down%20on%20fully%20remote%20work%2C%20including%20Amazon%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20Meta.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWant%20a%20promotion%3F%20Get%20into%20the%20office%20and%20soak%20up%20the%20knowledge%20within%20its%20walls%2C%20Google's%20former%20CEO%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20companies%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-employees-open-letter-aws-ceo-office-return-rto-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efaced%20resistance%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20requiring%20staff%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-requiring-return-to-office-rto-mandate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn%20to%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Eric%20Schmidt%20said%20asking%20workers%20to%20come%20back%20is%20partly%20for%20%26quot%3Btheir%20own%20benefit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchmidt%2C%20who%20ran%20Google%20from%202001%20to%202011%20as%20CEO%2C%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D2Zg--ouGl7c%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20recent%20episode%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Diary%20of%20A%20CEO%26quot%3B%20podcast%20that%20he%20has%20a%20%26quot%3Bstrong%20view%26quot%3B%20that%20staff%20should%20work%20in%20person%20to%20gain%20the%20types%20of%20experiences%20that%20remote%20work%20can't%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20a%20young%20executive%2C%20I%20knew%20nothing%20of%20what%20I%20was%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20Schmidt%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20literally%20was%20just%20lucky%20to%20be%20there%2C%20and%20I%20learned%20by%20hanging%20out%20at%20the%20water%20cooler%2C%20going%20to%20meetings%2C%20hanging%20out%2C%20being%20in%20the%20hallway.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20knowledge%20acquired%20from%20being%20in%20office%20was%20%26quot%3Bcentral%26quot%3B%20to%20his%20later%20promotions%2C%20Schmidt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20in%20your%2020s%2C%20you%20want%20to%20be%20in%20an%20office%20because%20that's%20how%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20promoted%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELive%20Data%20Technologies%20conducted%20an%20analysis%20of%202%20million%20white-collar%20workers%20and%20found%20that%2C%20over%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20the%20fully%20remote%20workers%20were%20promoted%2031%25%20less%20often%20than%20their%20hybrid%20or%20fully%20in-office%20peers%2C%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Flifestyle%2Fcareers%2Fremote-workers-are-losing-out-on-promotions-8219ec63%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchmidt%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20%26quot%3Backnowledge%26quot%3B%20that%2C%20in%20some%20industries%20that%20have%20been%20studied%2C%20the%20flexibility%20of%20working%20from%20home%20can%20increase%20productivity.%20Many%20people%20who%20want%20to%20be%20remote%20have%20legitimate%20commuting%20or%20family%20concerns%2C%20and%20there%20is%20data%20indicating%20that%20productivity%20is%20%26quot%3Bslightly%20higher%26quot%3B%20when%20remote%20work%20is%20allowed%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20least%20for%20the%20industries%20that%20have%20been%20studied%2C%20there's%20evidence%20that%20allowing%20that%20flexibility%20from%20work%20from%20home%20increases%20productivity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20happen%20to%20like%20it%2C%20but%20I%20want%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20science%20is%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20studied%20the%20hot-button%20topic%20with%20conflicting%20results.%20A%202023%20Goldman%20Sachs%20report%20that%20examined%20multiple%20studies%20suggested%20the%20varying%20conclusions%20could%20be%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-wfh-productivity-impact-no-consensus-goldman-sachs-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edifferences%20in%20study%20design%20and%20how%20researchers%20measure%20productivity%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudies%20have%20also%20suggested%20that%20being%20fully%20remote%20decreases%20workers'%20productivity.%20A%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsiepr.stanford.edu%2Fpublications%2Fworking-paper%2Fevolution-working-home%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20by%20Stanford's%20Institute%20for%20Economic%20Policy%20Research%20(SIEPR)%20indicated%20that%20fully%20remote%20work%20led%20to%20a%2010%25%20decrease%20in%20productivity%20compared%20to%20fully%20in-person%20work%2C%20though%20hybrid%20work%20appeared%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Bno%20impact%20on%20productivity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20many%20execs%20praised%20the%20flexibility%20of%20hybrid%20schedules%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20several%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-rto-billionaire-ceo-threaten-fire-workers-wfh-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebackpedaled%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20years%20since.%20Companies%2C%20including%20Amazon%2C%20JPMorgan%2C%20and%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20have%20ditched%20their%20remote%20work%20policies%20for%20full%20return-to-office%20mandates%2C%20with%20some%20even%20threatening%20to%20track%20performance%20or%20terminate%20those%20who%20don't%20comply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20have%20moved%20to%20a%20hybrid%20model.%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20said%C2%A0in%202023%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-update-meta-staff-remote-work-policy-lay-offs-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperformance%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%20Meta%20showed%20that%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20who%20work%20from%20home%20are%20not%20efficient%2C%20and%20engineers%20who%20come%20to%20the%20office%20get%20more%20work%20done.%26quot%3B%20Meta%20now%20requires%20employees%20to%20work%20at%20least%20three%20days%20a%20week%20from%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-openai-ceo-career-net-worth-ycombinator-prepper-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20Fortune%20Magazine%20one%20of%20the%20tech%20industry's%20%26quot%3Bworst%20mistakes%26quot%3B%20was%20to%20allow%20employees%20to%20go%20%26quot%3Bfull%20remote%20forever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchmidt%20expressed%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-google-ceo-losing-ai-race-staff-work-from-home-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimilar%20sentiments%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20an%20April%20lecture%20at%20Stanford%20University%2C%20saying%20that%20Google%20is%20losing%20out%20to%20AI%20rivals